ervices/word-coordinates-service"}], "rights": ["<p>The Library of Congress believes that the newspapers in Chronicling America are in the public domain or have no known copyright restrictions.  Newspapers published in the United States more than 95 years ago are in the public domain in their entirety. Any newspapers in Chronicling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 13.655856, "shard": "09", "shelf_id": "sn83045217, 1921-01-15, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/mthi", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["cascade county", "great falls (mont.)", "montana", "great falls", "cascade county (mont.)", "newspapers", "united states", "cascade"], "subject_headings": ["Great Falls (Mont.)--Newspapers", "Cascade County (Mont.)--Newspapers", "Montana--Cascade County", "Montana--Great Falls", "United States--Montana--Cascade--Great Falls"], "subjects": [{"cascade": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:cascade&fo=json"}, {"cascade county": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:cascade+county&fo=json"}, {"cascade county (mont.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:cascade+county+%28mont.%29&fo=json"}, {"great falls": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:great+falls&fo=json"}, {"great falls (mont.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:great+falls+%28mont.%29&fo=json"}, {"montana": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:montana&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2023-07-05T16:24:32.128Z", "title": "Great Falls tribune (Great Falls, Mont.), January 15, 1921", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045217/1921-01-15/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045217/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn83045217"], "batch": ["mthi_bison_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1921", "description": ["Daily 32nd year (Jan. 11, 1921)- Publication suspended Oct. 20-Dec. 18, 1974. Also issued on microfilm from Bell & Howell Information and Learning. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Latest issue consulted: 115th year, no. 354 (Apr. 30, 2000)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:15.450Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-15", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-15"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045217/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [47.506453, -111.306019], "location": ["cascade county", "montana", "great falls", "united states", "cascade"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-111.306019, 47.506453], "number": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045217/1922-12-31/ed-1/", "new york pub libr res libr", "sn83025311", "new york state - wc7", "microfilm service copy", "sn83045217", "720", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045217/1921-01-11/ed-1/", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "1", "2025-05-23t21:30:26", "sn84024808", "franklin d roosevelt libr", "9374534", "montana hist soc libr", "online resource", "library of congress", "2025-06-27t06:58:00", "original", "center for res libr, newsp proj", "2378-850x"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Tribune"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "great falls tribune (great falls, mont.) 1921-current", "serial and government publications division", "catalog", "chronicling america"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 86.01593, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["cascade county", "great falls (mont.)", "american newspapers", "montana", "great falls", "cascade county (mont.)", "newspapers", "united states", "cascade"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:07:48.184Z", "title": "Great Falls tribune", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045217/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2015218726/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1921", "dates": ["[1921 TO 9999]"], "description": ["Daily Began with thirty-second year (January 11, 1921). Publication suspended Oct. 20-Dec. 18, 1974. Also issued on microfilm from Bell & Howell Information and Learning. Description based on: Thirty-second year (January 11, 1921); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 29, 2015). Latest issue consulted: Thirty-fifth year (December 31, 1922) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 29, 2015)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:04.893Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2015218726/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["cascade county", "montana", "great falls", "united states", "cascade"], "number": ["2015218726", "online resource", "2015218694", "232117718", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2378-8518"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Tribune"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division", "great falls tribune (great falls, montana) 1921-current [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 76.901695, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["great falls (mont.)", "cascade county", "electronic journals", "periodicals", "montana", "great falls", "cascade county (mont.)", "newspapers", "united states", "cascade"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:51:50.551Z", "title": "Great Falls tribune", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2015218726/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272187/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["sutherlin, r. n."], "date": "1875", "dates": ["[1875 TO 1943]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. 1, no. 1 (November 25, 1875); ceased January 7, 1943. \"A Journal Devoted to Agriculture, Livestock, Home Reading, and General News.\". \"Pioneer agricultural and stock journal of Montana.\". Issues from 1925-1943 consists entirely of Montana News Association inserts with no independent content. Place of publication varies: Diamond City, Mont., Nov. 25, 1875-Nov. 20, 1879; White Sulphur Springs, Mont., Dec. 4, 1879-Mar. 24, 1904; Great Falls, Mont., Mar. 31, 1904-Jan. 7, 1943. Editor: R.N. Sutherlin. Description based on: Vol. 1, no. 1 (November 25, 1875); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 18, 2013). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 5, no. 5 (Dec. 18, 1879) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 18, 2013)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:24.080Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272187/", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["broadwater", "diamond city", "meagher", "montana", "great falls", "white sulphur springs", "united states", "cascade"], "number": ["2013272187", "2332-7537", "online resource", "862979362", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division", "rocky mountain husbandman (diamond city, m.t.) 1875-1943 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 49.941692, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["broadwater", "diamond city", "meagher", "great falls (mont.)", "electronic journals", "montana", "newspapers", "great falls", "white sulphur springs (mont.)", "white sulphur springs", "diamond city (mont.)", "united states", "cascade"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:49:47.660Z", "title": "Rocky Mountain husbandman", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2013272187/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218354/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1918", "dates": ["[1918 TO 1918]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with volume 2, number 3 (September 14, 1918); ceased October 12, 1918. Official organ of: National Nonpartisan League of the State of Montana. Description based on: Volume 2, number 3 (September 14, 1918); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014). Latest issue consulted: Volume 2, number 6 (October 5, 1918) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014). Montana nonpartisan (Online)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:25.703Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218354/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["great falls", "montana", "united states", "cascade"], "number": ["online resource", "2014218354", "879343459", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2372-885x"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "montana leader (great falls, montana) 1918-1918 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 49.941692, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["great falls (mont.)", "national nonpartisan league", "montana", "great falls", "newspapers", "united states", "cascade"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:50:11.310Z", "title": "Montana leader", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2014218354/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218355/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1918", "dates": ["[1918 TO 1929]"], "description": ["Weekly <Oct. 9-30, 1922> Began with volume 2, number 8 (October 19, 1918). Ceased in 1922? Last issue located: Vol. 5, no. 8 [i.e. 9] (Oct. 30, 1922). Place of publication varies: Great Falls, Oct. 19, 1918-May 7, 1921; Billings, June 10-<Oct. 30>, 1922. Suspended: Nov. 16-23, 1918; June 1921-May 1922. Official organ of: National Nonpartisan League in the State of Montana. Description based on: Volume 2, number 8 (October 19, 1918); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014). Latest issue consulted: Volume 3, number 51 (December 20, 1919) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:25.703Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218355/", "image_url": [], "index": 9, "language": ["english"], "location": ["montana", "cascade", "great falls", "yellowstone", "united states", "billings"], "number": ["online resource", "2014218355", "2372-8884", "879345154", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the montana nonpartisan (great falls, montana) 1918-192? [online re