"https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_bison_ver01/data/sn83045217/00295860728/1921011501/0016.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83045217/1921-01-15/ed-1/?sp=5"], "batch": ["mthi_bison_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/montana/", "2/united states/montana/cascade/", "3/united states/montana/cascade/great falls/"], "contributor": ["montana historical society; helena, mt"], "date": "1921-01-15", "dates": ["1921-01-15"], "description": ["NAMED BY Every Member of Old Board on List of Nominees Is ReElected Annual Reports Heard Work Planned Twenty director of the Great Falls Commercial club for 1921 were elected at the annual meeting of the members in the palm room of the Hotel Rainbow Friday night A feature f the election was that ten of the members of the retiring board nominated all were re elected The membership of the board wag increased from 19 to 20 because of a tie vote between Harry Newman and F E Beatty Each will have a half vote until some other members retire from the board for any reason The new directors are F E Beaty manager State Life In surance company W A Bertke manager Great Falls Gas company A T Breitenstein manager Hotel Hainbow Frank Brown vice president Great Falls Meat company L L Callaway attorney Clarence Conrad Conrad Grocery company Fred Fligman president Paris Dry Goods company S S Ford vice president Great Falls National bank W II George president W II George company F J Gies president F J Gies com pany George Grover proprietor Great Falls Monumental works A 1 Ileaney state distributor Velie agency J R"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-07-03T13:44:48.443Z", "group": ["ndnp/mthi", "montana-historical-society-helena-mt-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83045217/1921-01-15/ed-1/?sp=5", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/im